   ```java
   @PostMapping("/login")
   public String login(@RequestParam String username, HttpSession session) {
       // Perform login logic
       User user = userService.findByUsername(username);
       session.setAttribute("user", user);
       return "redirect:/dashboard";
   }
   ```

### 2. **Check for Session Expiry**
   - If the session has expired, the session attribute will no longer be available. You can handle this by checking if the session is valid or by setting a session timeout in your application configuration.

   ```java
   @GetMapping("/dashboard")
   public String dashboard(HttpSession session) {
       User user = (User) session.getAttribute("user");
       if (user == null) {
